rComments: Deeply committed instructor. Conscientious of the needs of her students. She intentionally slowed down the course to ensure that students had a better grasp of the material. She once hand-illustrated a case to clarify its facts and emailed the image out. Difficult exams that reward those students who prepare strategically.
Such a kind lady.  May seem weird and unusually engaged in the material at first, but this is because she knows it so well and is very passionate.
It's true...exams are BRUTAL. But she's an extremely clear lecturer, friendly, available for help. The curve is your friend if you go to class and actually try.
Life saver for my 1st year con. law. Clear and concise.

Sorry, but she wears her politics on her sleave.  The love-hate nature of the comments show how people respond to this to the extent they align with them.  Not objective enough.  Readings WAY too much, social science articles rep 1 POV. Talks too long, too much. Discussions kept "moral" and reactionary, little room for nuance or alternate views.
If only everyone threw themselves into their jobs like Rogerson does!  It takes a couple months to get used to her mannerisms but you'll fall for her eventually. Clear, dedicated, one of the best.
I think anyone who has anything bad to say about Prof. Rogerson probably doesnt understand the material.
Absolutely, the worst professor in the law school.  Unclear, repetitive, and absolutely mind-numbingly boring.  Avoid her at all costs!!!  She is TERRIBLE!!  Plus the exams are WAY too hard.
She's a little too excited and perky.  Also, she tends to ramble on a little too much making the issue much more complicated than it really is.  Definately has a certain sex appeal to her.
Prof. Rogerson is totally nice. She brought us candy at hallowe'en. What more do you want? Don't disagree with her- if you are WRONG, dork. Wicked prof.
She's a great prof and very approachable and knowledgeable.  Her exams are long and hard, though, but her teaching style makes up for it.
The worst course ever--don't disagree with her on exam
An amazing professor: extremely helpful and smart
